title.narrative: Mothers and other caregivers in targeted localities have improved skills and knowledge on key family practices

description.narrative: Over 882,500 mothers were more aware of recommended IYCF practices and have enhanced knowledge of key family-based actions including breastfeeding, handwashing at critical times, sleeping under LLINS and home management of diarrhea using ORS. A large number of community platforms, i.e. 3,000 mothers' support groups have strengthened capacities to support the delivery of key messages on health and nutrition interventions across Darfur, Kordofan states, Blue Nile, White Nile, Senna and the East of Sudan (Kassala, Gedaref and Red Sea). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
